{"blocks":[{"key":"6pp0c","text":"Take plates that require coating and label.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dnsj0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9h9t0","text":"Thaw an aliquot of Geltrex/DMEM/F12 (1:1 mix) on ice. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6varb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aggp1","text":"Prepare an aliquot of 22 ml cold DMEM/F12 = keep on ice.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":57,"length":1,"key":0}],"data":[]},{"key":"9397d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"e1sof","text":"On ice: Dilute 450 ul of 1:1 Geltrex (50X) ~1:50 into 22 ml cold DMEM/F12 medium for a final dilution of 1:100. Empirical determination of the optimal coating concentration for your application may be required. Volumes can be adjusted accordingly. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":7,"style":"bold"},{"offset":60,"length":5,"style":"bold"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3k96r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"acrg6","text":"Add a sufficient amount of diluted Geltrex solution to cover the entire area onto growth surface (100 ul/well in 96-well plate; 0.5 ml/well for 24-well and 4-well Ibidi imaging dish; 1 ml for 35 mm dish, 3 ml for 60 mm dish, i.e. 0.14 ml/cm2 --> 1 ml per 6-well dish; 8 ml per T75 flask). 
 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"a45t6","text":"Coat the dish and place in incubator (37C) for 60 min (no need to seal).  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":73,"length":1,"key":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"2d3hr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"f105p","text":"Afterwards, take the plates that you will need for cell seeding out to room temperature for minimum 30 min. Store the remaining plates at 4C for up to 2 weeks (best for only 1 week to be on the safe side; parafilm to avoid drying out).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"48fqq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3frg7","text":"Do not allow coated surface to dry out and maintain a storage temperature of 2 to 8°C to avoid premature gelling.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":115,"style":"bold"}],"entityRanges":[{"offset":114,"length":1,"key":2}],"data":[]},{"key":"5kghk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b8m28","text":"At time of use, aspirate GeltrexTM coating and immediately plate cells in pre-equilibrated cell culture medium. No rinsing! 








